# Data Fetching Patterns

## React Query (TanStack Query v5)

All client-side market data fetching goes through custom hooks in `hooks/FMP/`.
All Supabase data fetching goes through custom hooks in `hooks/`.

```ts
// ✅ hooks/FMP/useQuote.ts
export function useQuote(symbol: string) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['quote', symbol],
    queryFn: () => fetch(`/api/fmp/quote?symbol=${symbol}`).then(r => r.json()),
    enabled: !!symbol,
    staleTime: 60_000, // market data: 1 min
  });
}
```

```ts
// ✅ hooks/usePortfolio.ts — Supabase data
export function usePortfolio() {
  const supabase = createBrowserClient();
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['portfolio'],
    queryFn: async () => {
      const { data, error } = await supabase.from('tblPortfolio').select('*, tblPortfolioPositions(*)');
      if (error) throw error;
      return data;
    },
  });
}
```

## Mutations

Use `useMutation` with `onSuccess` query invalidation:

```ts
const addPosition = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (position) => supabase.from('tblPortfolioPositions').insert(position),
  onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['portfolio'] }),
});
```

## FMP API Proxy Rules

- Never import FMP base URL or API key in client code.
- All FMP routes live at `app/api/fmp/[endpoint]/route.ts`.
- Pass symbol/params as query strings: `/api/fmp/quote?symbol=AAPL`.
- Return `Response.json(data)` — do not forward FMP error objects to the client as-is; normalize first.

## staleTime Guidelines

| Data type | staleTime |
|-----------|-----------|
| Real-time quote | 30–60s |
| Daily OHLCV / sectors | 5 min |
| Earnings calendar | 1 hour |
| Income statements | 24 hours |
| User portfolio / watchlist | 0 (always fresh) |
